Krish Naik's course, "Master the theory, practice,and math behind Data Science,Machine Learning,Deep Learning,NLP with end to end projects" offers a comprehensive curriculum designed to guide learners from foundational concepts to advanced applications in data science. The course encompasses over 99.10 hours of content spread across 449 lectures, covering topics such as machine learning, natural language processing (NLP), MLOps, and deployment strategies. It emphasizes both theoretical understanding and practical implementation, featuring end-to-end projects that provide hands-on experience.

While I would like to give a 5 star rating for covering all the important topics, this course lacks the patience to explain the details that are required for a beginner in the field. If you have the mental energy to read between the lines and fill the gaps in the course, you can still complete. Else, this course is a bit difficult. It also looks like some videos posted here in the course are brought from another course elsewhere as the instructor keeps mentioning that there was a certain concept discussed earlier which was never discussed in the first place. Instructor misrepresents and misuses mathematical notations such as using eta for epsilon and epsilon for eta. I mean such mistakes are a no brainer and someone who has an attention to detail would not find it pleasing (which is a basic skill for a data scientist). I would second with the courses posted by Jose Portilla who explains concepts in a much better way and easy to follow along. Overall it is such a shame that this course despite of the great potential it had, is one among the falling stars.
